<p>I'm trying to determine whether the first char of the "sentence" string is capital or not. The program runs fine, but test run gives an array index out of range error. I can't understand the problem.</p>  <pre><code>public class CapitalOrNot {     public static void Main()     {         string sentence = "Asdafasda";         string UpOrLow = UpperOrLower(sentence);         Console.WriteLine("First char is " + UpOrLow);     }      public static string UpperOrLower(string mj)     {         if (char.IsUpper(mj[0]))         {             mj = "upper";         }         else mj = "lower";          return mj;     } } </code></pre>